Accelerator Pedal position 2 sensor short circuit to battery
Oorzaak: The controller measures a voltage above 2425mV for at least 100ms on pin 55 of connector A
Effect:
- When only accelerator pedal position 2 is faulty, the machine will go into limp home mode (reduced functionality to go to the workshop)
- When both accelerator pedal positions are faulty, the engine will only run at low idle speed
- The accelerator pedal position 2 is a safety critical input, therefor the fault will only be reset after a key cycle
Aangeraden actie:
- The accelerator pedal position circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltage in the accelerator pedal position 2 circuit, valid range is between 575 - 2075 mV
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 5V
- Measure the grounding of the accelerator pedal position 2 circuit, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace accelerator pedal

Park brake pressure sensor short circuit to ground
Oorzaak: The controller measures a current below 1000 µA for at least 100ms on pin 66 of connector A
Effect:
- The park brake telltale will blink at 2 Hz in the dashboard view
- The park brake status will be broadcasted as "Error" on the CAN bus, therefor 3rd party systems (Engine, Transmission, etc) may report faultcodes as well
Aangeraden actie:
- The park brake pressure sensor circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the current of the park brake pressure sensor, valid range is between 4 and 20 mA
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be equal to KL15 voltage
- Replace park brake pressure sensor

OI Message TimeOut error
Oorzaak: The controller has not received the OI CAN message for 50s from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
Effect: The controller can't determine the water in fuel status, since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the water in fuel telltale and pop-up won't be activated.
Aangeraden actie:
- When the OI Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration

- When the OI Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the engine controller and/or engine related subsystems

Differential lock state - central rear short circuit to battery
Oorzaak: The controller measures a voltage above 965mV for at least 100ms on pin 46 of connector B. Note: faultcode is only applicable for a diff. lock proximity sensor configuration and not for a diff. lock switch
Effect: When the differential lock state can't be determined by the controller, the system won't be able to display the current state.
Aangeraden actie:
'- The diff lock engaged circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 24V
- Measure the grounding of the diff lock proximity sensor or switch, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace diff lock proximity sensor or switch

Omschrijving: Differential lock state - central rear short circuit to ground
Oorzaak: The controller measures a voltage below 50mV for at least 100ms on pin 46 of connector B. Note: faultcode is only applicable for a diff. lock proximity sensor configuration and not for a diff. lock switch
Effect: When the differential lock state can't be determined by the controller, the system won't be able to display the current state.
Aangeraden actie:
- The diff lock engaged circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 24V

- Replace diff lock proximity sensor or switch

Service Brake Pressure short circuit to ground
Oorzaak: The controller measures a voltage below 1mA for at least 100ms on pin 65 of connector A
Effect: The controller is not able to determine the service brake pressure, therefor the controller can't determine if the brake pedal is pressed. Functions depending on the service brake might work
Aangeraden actie:
- The service brake pressure circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the current of the service brake pressure sensor, valid range is between 4 - 20mA
- Measure the grounding of the service brake pressure circuit, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace service brake pressure sensor

KL50 high side output short circuit to battery
Oorzaak: The controller measures a current below 500mA for at least 100ms on pin 18 of connector A
Effect:
The engine may not stop cranking, when the ignition if on.  Or the engine doesn't crank.
Note: the Volvo engine start via CAN
Aangeraden actie:
- The engine start circuit is partly described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2 and partly described in the Electic Diagram of the engine
- Measure the voltages in engine start circuit to find the short circuit to battery
- Measure the voltages in the engine start circuit to find the open load
- Check the fuses in the engine start circuit
- Replace KL50 engine start relay

Omschrijving: KL50 high side output short circuit to ground
Oorzaak: The controller measures a current above 1000mA for at least 100ms on pin 18 of connector A
Effect:
The engine doesn't crank.
Note: the Volvo engine start via CAN
Aangeraden actie:
- The engine start circuit is partly described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2 and partly described in the Electic Diagram of the engine
- Measure the voltages / resistance in engine start circuit to find the short circuit to ground
- Replace KL50 engine start relay

SHUTDN Message TimeOut error
Oorzaak: The controller has not received the SHUTDN CAN message for 5000 ms from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
Effect: The controller can't determine wait to start lamp status since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the wait to start telltale won't be shown on the display
Aangeraden actie:
- When the SHUTDN Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration

- When the SHUTDN Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the engine controller and/or engine related subsystems

Foutcode: Parking trailer brake air pressure sensor
Omschrijving: Parking Trailer Brake Air Pressure sensor current below normal or open circuit
Oorzaak: The controller measures a voltage below 1mA for at least 100ms on pin 8 of connector B
Effect: The controller is not able to determine the pressure of air circuit 3, therefor the controller can't broadcast the pressure to other systems. Functions depending on the air pressure of circuit 3 may function incorrect
Aangeraden actie:
- The air pressure circuit 3 is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the current of the air presssure circuit 3  sensor, valid range is between 4 - 20mA
- Measure the grounding of the air pressure circuit 3 , make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace air pressure circuit 3

Foutcode: Parking trailer brake air pressure sensor
Omschrijving: Parking Trailer Brake Air Pressure sensor current above normal or grounded circuit
Oorzaak: The controller measures a voltage above 21mA for at least 100ms on pin 65 of connector B
Effect: The controller is not able to determine the pressure of air circuit 1, therefor the controller can't broadcast the pressure to other systems and determine the brake pressure for the front axle. Functions depending on the air pressure of circuit 1 may function incorrect.
Aangeraden actie:
- The air pressure circuit 3 is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the current of the air presssure circuit 3  sensor, valid range is between 4 - 20mA
- Measure the grounding of the air presssure circuit 3 , make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace air presssure circuit 3

Omschrijving: Air Pressure Circuit 1 short circuit to battery
Oorzaak: The controller measures a voltage above 4500mV for at least 100ms on pin 64 of connector A
Effect: The controller is not able to determine the pressure of air circuit 1, therefor the controller can't broadcast the pressure to other systems and determine the brake pressure for the front axle. Functions depending on the air pressure of circuit 1 may function incorrect.
Aangeraden actie:
- The air pressure circuit 1 is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltage in the air pressure circuit 1, valid range is between 1000 - 4000 mV
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 24V
- Measure the grounding of the air pressure circuit 1, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace air pressure circuit 1 sensor

Omschrijving: P4677 - Sae j1939 multiplexing PGN timeout error - abnormal update rate
AT1T1I1 Message TimeOut error
Oorzaak: The controller has not received the AT1T1I1 CAN message for 5000ms from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
Effect: The controller can't determine the DEF level and DEF level low indicator, since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the display is not able to show information in relation to the diesel exhaust fluid
Aangeraden actie:
- When the AT1T1I1 Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration
- When the AT1T1I1 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)

Work Light Cabin Front output short circuit to battery
Oorzaak: The controller measures a current below 20mA for at least 100ms on pin 81 of connector A
Effect: The controller is not able to control the work light front, therefor the work light front may or may not illuminate. A short to circuit to battery may result in a group switch 2 error and may deactivate outputs 73 - 81 of connector A.
Aangeraden actie:
- The work light front circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltages in work light front circuit to find the short circuit to battery
- Measure the voltages in the work light front circuit to find the open load
- Check the fuses in the work light front circuit
- Replace work light front

5th Wheel Lift Lower Joystick 1 sensor short circuit to battery
Oorzaak: The controller measures a voltage above 4750mV for at least 100ms on pin 67 of connector A
Effect:
- When only one of the two joystick signals is faulty, the 5th wheel can still be operated 
- When both joystick signals are faulty, the 5th wheel can't be operated anymore
- The 5th wheel joystick is a safety critical input, therefor the fault will only be reset after a key cycle
Aangeraden actie:
- The 5th th wheel joystick circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltage in the 5th wheel joystick signal 1 circuit, valid range is between 4500 - 500 mV
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 5V
- Measure the grounding of the 5th wheel joystick signal 1 circuit, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace 5th wheel joytstick

Omschrijving: 5th Wheel Lift Lower Joystick 1 sensor short circuit to ground
Oorzaak: The controller measures a voltage below 250mV for at least 100ms on pin 67 of connector A
Effect:
- When only one of the two joystick signals is faulty, the 5th wheel can still be operated 
- When both joystick signals are faulty, the 5th wheel can't be operated anymore
- The 5th wheel joystick is a safety critical input, therefor the fault will only be reset after a key cycle
Aangeraden actie:
- The 5th th wheel joystick circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltage in the 5th wheel joystick signal 1 circuit, valid range is between 4500 - 500 mV
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 5V
- Measure the grounding of the 5th wheel joystick signal 1 circuit, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace 5th wheel joytstick

Omschrijving: 5th Wheel Lift Lower Joystick 1 root cause not known
Oorzaak: The controller determines an issue on pin 67 of connector A. Specific root cause can't be determined. Potential hardware, software, firmware or configuration issue
Effect:
- When only one of the two joystick signals is faulty, the 5th wheel can still be operated 
- When both joystick signals are faulty, the 5th wheel can't be operated anymore
- The 5th wheel joystick is a safety critical input, therefor the fault will only be reset after a key cycle
Aangeraden actie:
- Contact the aftersales department for support via the portal

In order to facilitate adequate support please supply the following information:
1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)
2) Log file from DIM, of the faulty scenario
3) Photo or movie of the behavior or of the DIM e.g. Dashboard view, Faultcodes view, IO Check view, CAN network check view, About menu view
4) Updated software or parameter set recently, from Terberg or 3rd party systems e.g. Engine, Transmission? If so, please supply us with details.

Omschrijving: Terberg Joystick Forward Gear Button signal error
Oorzaak: The controllers receives an "Error" status in the forward gear button CAN signal
Effect: The controller can't determine the forward gear request, therefor the forward driving direction will not be requested from the transmission
Aangeraden actie:
- Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
- Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the joystick
- Replace joystick

Aangeraden actie:
- Contact the aftersales department for support via the portal

In order to facilitate adequate support please supply the following information:
1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)
2) Log file from DIM, of the faulty scenario
3) Photo or movie of the behavior or of the DIM e.g. Dashboard view, Faultcodes view, IO Check view, CAN network check view, About menu view
4) Updated software or parameter set recently, from Terberg or 3rd party systems e.g. Engine, Transmission? If so, please supply us with details.

Omschrijving: Voltage below normal or shorted to ground
Oorzaak: Output pin 31 is causing this issue. This pin is connected to the supply pin (pin 2) of the footbrake module. Perhaps due to a wire break or short circuit to ground.
Effect: The footbrake module is not functioning
Aangeraden actie: First check the wiring between pin 31 of the ATCC2 and pin 2 of the footbrake module. Second check the footbrake module itself for correct functioning.

Omschrijving: Sensor Supply 5 Volt short circuit to battery
Oorzaak: The controller measures a voltage above 5100mV for at least 100ms on pin 31 of connector A
Effect: The controller can't supply the sensors with 5V supply, therefor sensors and switches may report errors
Aangeraden actie:
- The 5V supply circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltage valid range is between 4900 mV - 5100mV
- Check fuses that supply 24V of the controller

Brake Light output short circuit to battery
Oorzaak: The controller measures a current below 20mA for at least 100ms on pin 78 of connector A
Effect: The controller is not able to control the brake light, therefor the brake light may or may not illuminate. A short to circuit to battery may result in a group switch 2 error and may deactivate outputs 73 - 81 of connector A.
Aangeraden actie:
- The brake light circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltages in brake light circuit to find the short circuit to battery
- Measure the voltages in the brake light circuit to find the open load
- Check the fuses in the brake light circuit
- Replace brake light

Omschrijving: Brake Light output short circuit to ground
Oorzaak: The controller measures a current above 250mA for at least 100ms on pin 78 of connector A
Effect: The controller is not able to control the brake light, therefor the brake light may not illuminate.
Aangeraden actie:
- The brake light circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltages / resistance in brake light circuit to find the short circuit to ground
- Replace brake light

1 of the 2 emergency inputs is incorrect
Oorzaak: The controller measures voltage between 200mV and 500mv for at least 100ms on PIN 42B or 43B.
Effect: When the emergency button input state can't be determined by the controller, the emergency button may won't be able to stop the vehicle operation in emergency cases
Aangeraden actie:
The emergency shutdown circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 24V
- Measure the voltage on 42B and 43B, these must be equal to the supply voltage, when the buttons are released and 0V, when closed
- Both inputs must have the same outcome (open or closed)
- Replace emergency button

DPFC1 Message Time out error
Oorzaak: The controller has not received the DPFC1 CAN message for 5000 ms from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
Effect: The controller can't determine aftertreatment regeneration status since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the aftertreatment regeneration statusb  won't be shown on the display
Aangeraden actie:
- When the DPFC1 Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration

- When the DPFC1 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the engine controller and/or engine related subsystems

Effect: The controller can't determine the temperature of the transmission converter out temperature. Therefore the actual temperature and the temperature warnings will not be shown
Aangeraden actie:
- The transmission converter out temperature circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the resistance in the transmission converter out temperature circuit, valid range is between 20 Ohm - 40000 Ohm
- Measure the grounding  make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace sensor

In order to facilitate adequate support please supply the following information:
1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)
2) Log file from DIM, of the faulty scenario
3) Photo or movie of the behavior or of the DIM e.g. Dashboard view, Faultcodes view, IO Check view, CAN network check view, About menu view
4) Updated software or parameter set recently, from Terberg or 3rd party systems e.g. Engine, Transmission? If so, please supply us with details.

DLCC1 Message TimeOut error
Oorzaak: The controller has not received the DLCC1 CAN message for 5000 ms from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
Effect: The controller can't determine engine lamp status since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the engine malfunction lamps  won't be shown on the display
Aangeraden actie:
- When the DLCC1 Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration

- When the DLCC1 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the engine controller and/or engine related subsystems

Foutcode: Hella intelligent battery sensor (IBS) CAN node
Omschrijving: The YTCC detected that the status message from the Hella IBS is not available on the TB1CAN bus indicating that the Hella IBS CAN node is not available
Oorzaak: The YTCC did not receive any CAN messages from the Hella IBS CAN node within a certain timeframe
Effect: The YTCC is unable to determine the status of the 24V BMS. Without this information, optimalisation of the charging strategy for the 24V battery is not possible
Aangeraden actie: Open the CAN Network check menu and check if the IBS is available on the CAN Network. If the IBS is not available, not active or error check the CANbus, LINbus and power supply of the IBS. Also check if the LIN to CAN converter is operational. If it is available check if any message from source address 0x1E is present on the TB1CAN bus. If there is a message on the TB1CAN bus from the source address mentioned before check if the YTCC is operational. When the YTCC is operational try flashing the vehicle with the latest software set available for the vehicle. Try replacing the LIN to CAN converter, try replacing the IBS

Voltage above normal
Oorzaak: The voltage measured on pin 67 of the A connector is above the normal value
Effect: The first part of the brake pedal stroke (in which electronic braking is active) is not functioning correct. In DBW mode, protective stop will be activated
Aangeraden actie: Check pin 67A on the ATCC2 or check the connector on the brake pedal

Omschrijving: Voltage below normal
Oorzaak: The voltage measured on pin 67 of connector A is below the normal value
Effect:
In manual mode it is no longer possible to release control and switch to DBW Mode. Also a speed limiter will be applied.

In DBW mode a protective stop will be activated since the brake pedal state cannot be determined prevenet a proper functioning of the driver intervention via brake pedal
Aangeraden actie: Please check pin 67 of connector A

Omschrijving: Root cause unknown
Oorzaak: The controller determines an issue on pin 67 of connector A. Specific root cause can't be determined. Potential hardware, software, firmware or configuration issue
Effect:
In manual mode it is no longer possible to release control and switch to DBW Mode. Also a speed limiter will be applied.

In DBW mode a protective stop will be activated since the brake pedal state cannot be determined prevenet a proper functioning of the driver intervention via brake pedal
Aangeraden actie:
- Contact the aftersales department for support via the portal

In order to facilitate adequate support please supply the following information:
1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)
2) Log file from DIM, of the faulty scenario
3) Photo or movie of the behavior or of the DIM e.g. Dashboard view, Faultcodes view, IO Check view, CAN network check view, About menu view
4) Updated software or parameter set recently, from Terberg or 3rd party systems e.g. Engine, Transmission? If so, please supply us with details.

Omschrijving: Unintended steering
Oorzaak: In DBW mode, the requested steering angle is not reached or the steering angle did not move fast enough towards the requested steering angle. Perhaps something is wrong with the steering angle sensors or the steering calibration is off.
Effect: Protective stop will be triggered, automatic steering will be blocked
Aangeraden actie: Re-calibrate the DBW steering control. When something is wrong with the steering angle sensors, this will be noticed during calibration as well.

Omschrijving: PVED-CLS operating state invalid
Oorzaak: The steering controller is not in autonomous mode, while the vehicle is in DBW mode. This is most likely caused by a safe state triggered in the steering controller. It might be, but is less likely erratic CAN requests transmitted to the steering controller.
Effect: Protective stop will be triggered in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie:
Please check if the PVED is powered on and check if it is still properly connected to the TB2 CAN bus. This can be checked via the CAN network check menu on the display. In case the PVED is on and connected to the TB2 CAN, please contact the aftersales department for support via the portal

In order to facilitate adequate support please supply the following information:
1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)
2) Log file from DIM, of the faulty scenario
3) Photo or movie of the behavior or of the DIM e.g. Dashboard view, Faultcodes view, IO Check view, CAN network check view, About menu view
4) Updated software or parameter set recently, from Terberg or 3rd party systems e.g. Engine, Transmission? If so, please supply us with details.

Omschrijving: Condition Exists
Oorzaak: Something is wrong with the steering controller (PVED). It might be powered off, or not correctly communicating on the TB2 CAN bus. It is also possible the PVED is defect.
Effect: Speed limit of 5 km/h is activated in manual mode. Protective stop is activated in DBW mode.
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the PVED is powered on and check if it is still properly connected to the TB2 CAN bus. This can be checked via the CAN network check menu on the display. If this all looks ok, swapping the PVED might be needed.

Omschrijving:
The hydraulic oil temperature is high. When it becomes too high, the hydraulic application will be disabled.

When the hydraulic oil temperature becomes too high, the extra hydraulic application will be disabled.
Aangeraden actie: Let the hydraulic oil cool down

Omschrijving: The hydraulic oil temperature is too high, the extra hydraulic application is disabled
Aangeraden actie: Let the hydraulic oil cool down

Foutcode: Park brake release - pressure too low
Omschrijving: Pressure is smaller than 540 kpa while park brake is released
Oorzaak: Perhaps the park brake pressure sensor is faulty, or there might be a leak in the pneumatic system.
Effect: Speed limit of 5 km/h is activated in manual mode. Protective stop is activated in DBW mode.
Aangeraden actie: Check for air leaking from the pneumatic system. You should be able to hear air leaking. Otherwise swap the park brake pressure sensor

Foutcode: Park brake pressure released too fast
Omschrijving: The park brake pressure has been released too fast
Oorzaak:
The throttle valve might be missing in the park brake pneumatic system. The park brake pressure sensor might be faulty  or there might be a leak in the pneumatic system.

Note: please prevent cycling the park brake request any faster than 3 seconds as this will not give the pneumatic system enough time to reach some pressure points and will likely trigger a pressure monitoring safety function.
Effect: Speed limit of 5 km/h is activated in manual mode. Protective stop is activated in DBW mode.
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the throttle valve has been installed in the electronic park brake system. Check for air leaking from the pneumatic system. You should be able to hear air leaking. Otherwise swap the park brake pressure sensor

Omschrijving: No power due to engine off
Oorzaak:
This cause is fueltype specific:
Diesel: The engine is not running, therefore there is no hydraulic pressure.

EV: The hydraulic pump is not running
Effect: Power steering is disabled which in turn causes automatic steering to be in error
Aangeraden actie:
This is fueltype specific:
Diesel: Please start the engine. 

EV: Please check if the hydraulic pump is running (EAMS message on J1939)

If the steering power monitor function keeps failing, please check the hydraulic piping

Omschrijving: Data error

Effect:
When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
When in Manual mode it is no longer possible to switch to DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the DBW user is sending the DBW user 01 message contents correctly

Omschrijving: Message time-out

Effect:
When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
When in Manual mode it is no longer possible to switch to DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the DBW user is still connected and sending the DBW user 01 message at the correct update cycle of 20ms

Omschrijving: crc or message counter error

When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.

Aangeraden actie: Please check if the DBW user is sending the DBW user 01 message CRC and counter correctly

Omschrijving: Node time-out
Oorzaak: Messages from the PVED CAN Node have been not been received for several cycles (such as the STR_FB message or the STAT_message)
Effect: There is no communication with the PVED, therefore there is no possibily to steer in DBW Mode. Switching to DBW mode will be impossible. If you are already in DBW mode, a protective stop will be activated
Aangeraden actie:
Check the PVED node is online. This can be done with a canalyser or use the CAN network check in the DIM.

The nodes should have addres 16#13 for the main UC and 16#5A for the safety UC

Omschrijving: Spool calibration failure
Oorzaak: There was a problem during the steering calibration. A specific cause cannot be determined
Effect: The steering calibration cannot be completed
Aangeraden actie: Run the calibration procedure again

Omschrijving: Node time-out
Oorzaak: All messages transmitted by the YTCC2 on the TB1 CAN bus are not received by the ATCC2. The YTCC2 might be powered off or disconnected from the TB1 CAN bus.
Effect: The vehicle cannot be operated properly. Probably a lot of indications on  the DIM will also not function correctly.
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the YTCC2 is powered on and check if it is still properly connected to the TB1 CAN bus. This can be checked via the CAN network check menu on the display.

Omschrijving: Message time-out
Oorzaak: This message has not been received for over 500 ms
Effect: Status feedback of all signals in this messages are not received by the ATCC2, therefor the vehicle will not be able to operate in DBW mode.
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the YTCC2 is powered on and check if it is still properly connected to the TB1 CAN bus. This can be checked via the CAN network check menu on the display.

Omschrijving: Data error
Oorzaak: One of the signals in DBW user 04 messages is out of range. This could be the DBW control request, 5th wheel unlock request or 5th wheel height request
Effect:
When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
When in Manual mode it is no longer possible to switch to DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the DBW user is sending the DBW user 04 message contents correctly.

Omschrijving: Message time-out
Oorzaak: DBW user 05 message has not been received anymore for over 80 ms.
Effect:
When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
When in Manual mode it is no longer possible to switch to DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the DBW user is still connected and sending the DBW user 05 message at the correct update cycle of 20ms

Omschrijving: The electronic steering system is not calibrated
Oorzaak: Calibration not done after critical changes to vehicle
Effect: The steering system cannot properly determine the actual steering angle
Aangeraden actie: Please calibrate the steering system via the calibration menu on the display

Omschrijving: DBW User communication detected but messages not read by vehicle
Oorzaak:
Restoring the DBW User communication while vehicle controllers already running.
Possibly to high update rate of DBW user CAN messages.
Effect: DBW User messages will not be read
Aangeraden actie: Please perform a keycycle

Omschrijving: Cross check CORA velocity not valid
Oorzaak: CORA velocity determined based on individual wheels are both valid but deviate more than 2 km/h for at least 5 seconds
Effect: Safe vehicle speed is invalid resulting in protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: check everything that can influence the circumference of the front wheels e.g. tire pressure, tire wear, tire size but also the A/B pulse ring

Omschrijving: Data error
Oorzaak: One of the signals in DBW user 06 messages is out of range. This could be the service brake front request, service brake rear request or service brake trailer request
Effect:
When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
When in Manual mode it is no longer possible to switch to DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the DBW user is sending the DBW user 06 message contents correctly.

Omschrijving: Message time-out
Oorzaak: DBW user 06 message has not been received anymore for over 80 ms.
Effect:
When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
When in Manual mode it is no longer possible to switch to DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the DBW user is still connected and sending the DBW user 06 message at the correct update cycle of 20ms

Omschrijving: crc or message counter error
Oorzaak: The CRC check or counter of the DBW user 06 messages is incorrect.
Effect:
When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
When in Manual mode it is no longer possible to switch to DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the DBW user is sending the DBW user 06 message CRC and counter correctly

Omschrijving: Time-out or Checksum fault at PropB RTCC_CC1 Can message
Time-out or Checksum fault at PropB RTCC_CC2 Can message
Checksum fault in ZF SL1 Can message
Aangeraden actie: Check CAN Bus, Check Shift Lever

Omschrijving: The measured temperature is too high for the controller to operate. Output current reduced by 25%.
Aangeraden actie:
Cool the controller below the critical temperature. 
Increase airflow to the controller, reduce the current requested, and/or lower the ambient temperature.

Omschrijving: YTCC CC1 MEssage Time out error
The RT controller is not detected, timeout set
The RT controller message RTCC Limit is in timeout
The RT controller message RTCC Alive is in timeout
Data error
Oorzaak:
One of the signals in the YTCC2 05 messages is out of range. This could be among other things 5th wheel height or 5th wheel lock related .

The YTCC2 05 message is an internal message send between the YTCC2 and the ATCC2
Effect:
In manual mode: It will no longer be possible to switch to DBW mode and a speed limiter will be applied

In DBW Mode: A protective stop will be activated
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the YTCC2 is sending the YTCC2 05 message contents correctly.

Omschrijving: Message time-out
Oorzaak: YTCC2 05 message has not been received anymore for over 80 ms.
Effect:
When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
When in Manual mode it is no longer possible to switch to DBW mode and a speed limit is activated
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the YTCC2 is sending the YTCC2 05 message and check if CRC and counter value is correct

Omschrijving: crc or message counter error
Oorzaak: The CRC check of theYTCC2 05 message is incorrect.
Effect:
When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
When in Manual mode it is no longer possible to switch to DBW mode and a speed limit is activated
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the YTCC2 is sending the YTCC23 05 message CRC and counter correctly

Omschrijving: TCU1 MessageTimeout Error
Condition Exists
Oorzaak: The steering controller (PVED) is in autonomous mode, while the vehicle is in manual mode
Effect: Speed limiter of 5 km/h is activated.
Aangeraden actie:
- Contact the aftersales department for support via the portal

In order to facilitate adequate support please supply the following information:
1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)
2) Log file from DIM, of the faulty scenario
3) Photo or movie of the behavior or of the DIM e.g. Dashboard view, Faultcodes view, IO Check view, CAN network check view, About menu view
4) Updated software or parameter set recently, from Terberg or 3rd party systems e.g. Engine, Transmission? If so, please supply us with details.

Omschrijving: Current below normal
Oorzaak: Possibly a open connection, wirebreak or short circuit to ground
Effect: The brake valve will not function properly
Aangeraden actie: Check Pin 08B or 38B on the ATCC2 for a faulty connection

Omschrijving: Current above normal
Oorzaak: Possibly a short circuit to the battery
Effect: The brake valve will not function properly
Aangeraden actie: Check Pin 08B or 38B on the ATCC2 for a faulty connection

Omschrijving: Condition Exists
Oorzaak: The controller detects a problem with pin 8 or 38 of the B connector. Possibly a short circuit to ground or battery.
Effect: The brake valve will not function properly
Aangeraden actie: Check Pin 08B or 38B on the ATCC2 for a faulty connection

Omschrijving: The protective stop has been activated
Oorzaak: One of the safety functions detected a problem
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check other DTC's or check if one of the safety functions is violated. The safety functions can be found in the manual

Omschrijving: The safe stop has been activated
Oorzaak: A Safe Stop via a CAN request has been requested by the DBW User
Effect: The vehicle will activate a safe stop, bringing the vehicle to a safe standstill state
Aangeraden actie: Please check the CAN signal for safe stop request that is being send by the DBW User. Is the data correct?

Omschrijving: The safe stop has been activated
Oorzaak: A Safe Stop via a CAN request has been requested by the DBW User
Effect: The vehicle will activate a safe stop, bringing the vehicle to a safe standstill state
Aangeraden actie: Deactivate the safe stop via CAN request by not sending a "requested" signal from the DBW User to the DBW vehicle

Omschrijving: The emergency stop has been activated
Oorzaak: An emergency button has been pressed / the the signals of a button are invalid
Effect: The vehicle will activate an emergency stop, causing the vehicle to come to a standstill
Aangeraden actie: Check if a button is pressed. If this is not the case please check the wiring or the contacts inside the button

Omschrijving: The emergency stop has been activated
Oorzaak: An emergency button has been pressed
Effect: The vehicle will activate an emergency stop, causing the vehicle to come to a standstill
Aangeraden actie: Please reset the pressed emergency button by twisitng the button untill it pops out and perfrom a reset

Omschrijving: Node time-out
crc or message counter error
Message time-out
crc or message counter error
Message time-out
Unexpected park brake pressure
Oorzaak: The measured park brake pressure was incorrect. According to the measured pressure, the park brake was not applied and not released (so undefined)
Effect: A speed limiter will be activated in manual mode.
Aangeraden actie: Check pin 66 A of the YTCC2 controller. The YTCC2 measures the park brake pressure on this input pin and forwards it in the YTCC2_04 on the TB1 CAN bus, from which the ATCC2 receives it.

Omschrijving: Validation parameters data file error
Oorzaak: The file that contains the parameter data is invalid
Effect: The parameters cannot be validated, therefore the vehicle cannot be used
Aangeraden actie: Retry safe parameter validation.If that does not work, try updating the vehicle with the correct software package and rety.  If that does not work please contact the aftersales department for support via the portal.

Omschrijving: Validation parameters data file error
Validation parameters data open error
Validation parameters data open error
Oorzaak: There was a problem with opening the file that contains the parameters
Effect: The parameters cannot be validated, therefore the vehicle cannot be used
Aangeraden actie: Retry safe parameter validation.If that does not work, try updating the vehicle with the correct software package and rety.  If that does not work please contact the aftersales departmend for support via the portal.

Omschrijving: Validation parameters data save error
Oorzaak: There was a problem with saving the parameter values
Effect: The parameters cannot be validated, therefore the vehicle cannot be used
Aangeraden actie: Retry safe parameter validation.If that does not work, try updating the vehicle with the correct software package and rety.  If that does not work please contact the aftersales departmend for support via the portal.

Omschrijving: Validation parameters data save error
J1939 ZF Sl1 shifter node timeout
RRCC node timeout
Aangeraden actie: Node timeout

Omschrijving: Device contains test software, vehicle is not allowed to be shipped
Oorzaak: Something when wrong with selecting a software package
Effect: Do not use this software since some safety function might not be operational
Aangeraden actie: Flash latest released software package

Omschrijving: Service brake valves not calibrated
Oorzaak: The service brake calibration has not been executed succesfully.
Effect: The accuracy of the service brake valves might be compromised
Aangeraden actie: Please active service mode and calibrate the service brake valves

Omschrijving: The safe stop has been activated
Oorzaak: The safe stop via the hardwired interface has been activated unintentionally
Effect: The vehicle will activate a safe stop, bringing the vehicle to a safe standstill state
Aangeraden actie: Please check the wiring for the safe stop hardwired signal. Check if the signals are equivalent

Omschrijving: The safe stop has been activated
Oorzaak: A Safe Stop via the hardwired interface has been requested by the DBW User
Effect: The vehicle will activate a safe stop, bringing the vehicle to a safe standstill state
Aangeraden actie: Deactivate the safe stop request from the DBW User via the hardwired interface

Foutcode: Prot Stop Invalid DBW Gear Request
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to an invalid gear request
Oorzaak: The gear request send by the DBW User has an invalid value or does not pass the safety check
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check the data that is send in the signal "requested gear"

Foutcode: Prot Stop Invalid DBW Torque Request
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to an invalid torque request
Oorzaak: The torque request send by the DBW User has an invalid value or does not pass the safety check
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check the data that is send in the signal "requested torque"

Foutcode: Prot Stop Invalid DBW Service Brake Front Request
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to an invalid service brake front request
Oorzaak: An invalid value or discrepancy in the DBW Front service brake request has been detected
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check the value of the service brake front request send by the DBW User

Foutcode: Prot Stop Invalid DBW Service Brake Rear Request
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to an invalid service brake rear request
Oorzaak: An invalid value or discrepancy in the DBW Rear service brake request has been detected
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check the value of the service brake rear request send by the DBW User

Foutcode: Prot Stop Invalid DBW Service Brake Trailer Request
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to an invalid service brake trailer request
Oorzaak: An invalid value or discrepancy in the DBW trailer service brake request has been detected
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check the value of the service brake trailer request send by the DBW User

Foutcode: Prot Stop Auto Steering not enabled
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to inactive auto steering function
Oorzaak: The automatic steering function has encountered an error and is therefore not working properly anymore
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check if the conditions to automatically steer are ok. Check the PVED operating state. Check if the steering calibration has been done (correctly)

Foutcode: Prot Stop Safe speed not ok
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to an invalid safe speed determination
Oorzaak: The safe speed signals are not valid
Effect: Safe vehicle speed is invalid resulting in protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check the left and right vehicle speed signals on the CAN bus, possibly check the wiring of the encoders to the controller

Foutcode: Prot Stop Park Brake apply monitor not ok
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to the park brake apply monitor function
Oorzaak: The apply step of the monitoring function for the park brake has detected an error
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check if there is dirt in the valves, if the supply pressure is high enough or if there is a possible leak. Lastly check wiring to the valves

Foutcode: Prot Stop Park Brake release monitor not ok
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to the park brake release monitor function
Oorzaak: The release step of the monitoring function for the park brake has detected an error
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check if there is dirt in the valves, if the supply pressure is high enough or if there is a possible leak. Lastly check wiring to the valves

Foutcode: Prot Stop invalid park brake pressure
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to an invalid park brake pressure
Oorzaak: The park brake pressure in invalid
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check the park brake supply pressure, verify that the sensors are working properly and verify that the apply / release monitor function passes

Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to the driver intervention function
Oorzaak: The driver has requested an intervention via steering wheel or brake pedal while meeting the speed threshhold requirement
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Ask the driver if he is ok and once the safety driver clear the situation as "no danger" continue your driving

Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to a request from the YTCC2
Oorzaak: The YTCC2 has requested a protective stop because one of the safety functions in this controller has encountered an error
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check the other DTC's. It probably has to do with 5th wheel height control

Foutcode: Prot Stop by 5th wheel lock monitor
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due the 5th wheel lock monitor not ok
Oorzaak: The 5th wheel lock monitor safety function has encountered an error
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check the trailer coupled state. Check the kingpin sensor state, check the 5th wheel lock sensor state, check if the trailer was released unintentional

Foutcode: Prot Stop by Manual Takeover button not ok
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due the manual takeover button(s) not ok
Oorzaak: One or multiple of the manual take over buttons has an invalid state causing it to not work properly anymore
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please check the wiriing / contacts for each of the manual take over buttons

Foutcode: Prot Stop invalid brake pedal state
Omschrijving: Protective stop activated due to an invalid brake pedal state
Oorzaak: The brake pedal state is invalid
Effect: The vehicle will perfom a protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check the wiring for the brake pedal state.

Omschrijving: 5th wheel control blocked because of safe stop activation
Oorzaak: 5th wheel control has been blocked due to an safe stop request
Effect: Movement of the 5th wheel is not possible at this point in time, because a safe stop requires the vehicle to come to a standstill
Aangeraden actie: Please deactivate the safe stop and if done succesfully the 5th wheel should be able to be controlled again

Omschrijving: 5th wheel control blocked because of emergency stop activation
Oorzaak: 5th wheel control has been blocked due to an emergency stop request
Effect: Movement of the 5th wheel is not possible at this point in time, because an emergency stop requires the vehicle to come to a standstill
Aangeraden actie: Please deactivate the emergency stop and if done succesfully the 5th wheel should be able to be controlled again

Omschrijving: At least one of the safety related parameters is not correctly validated
Oorzaak: One of the safe parameters that has been entered does not match the defined parameters from the specification
Effect: The vehicle will prevent operation
Aangeraden actie: Go to the parameter validation menu and enter the correct values

Omschrijving: At least one of the safety related parameters is not correctly validated
Aangeraden actie: Go to the parameter validation menu and enter the correct values

Omschrijving: The driver has intervented the DBW operation via steering wheel
Oorzaak: The safety driver steered using the manual steering wheel
Effect: A driver intervention will be triggered causing a protective stop or a switch to manual mode depending on the vehicle speed
Aangeraden actie: Please ensure that the environment is safe and clear and then continue driving

Omschrijving: The driver has intervented the DBW operation via the brake pedal
Oorzaak: The safety driver intervened by using the brake pedal to apply service brake pressure
Effect: A driver intervention will be triggered causing a protective stop or a switch to manual mode depending on the vehicle speed
Aangeraden actie: Please ensure that the environment is safe and clear and then continue driving

Omschrijving: Auto steering control disabled due to invalid request
Oorzaak: The steering angle request recieved from the DBW user is invalid
Effect: Automatic steering will not be available and the vehicle will perform a protective stop
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the steering request signal is valid

Foutcode: Auto Steering Control disabled Safe stop
Omschrijving: Auto steering control disabled due to activated safe stop
Oorzaak: A safe stop has been activated
Effect: Automatic steering will be blocked while a safe stop is active
Aangeraden actie: Please deactive the safe stop to resume automatic steering

Omschrijving: Drive direction based on individual wheels are off opposite sign
Oorzaak: Drive direction based on individual wheels are opposite (one forward and the other reverse) for at least 100 ms
Effect: Safe vehicle speed is invalid resulting in protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check wheel speed A/B sensor and wiring

Foutcode: Left wheel speed A/B encoder failure
Omschrijving: Left wheel speed A/B is not valid
Oorzaak: Signal A and/or signal B is shorted to battery or ground
Effect: Safe vehicle speed is invalid resulting in protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check wheel speed A/B sensor and wiring

Foutcode: Right wheel speed A/B encoder failure
Omschrijving: Right wheel speed A/B is not valid
Oorzaak: Signal A and/or signal B is shorted to battery or ground
Effect: Safe vehicle speed is invalid resulting in protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check wheel speed A/B sensor and wiring

Foutcode: Steering Angle Calib Data File Error
Omschrijving: Steering angle calibratrion data file error
Oorzaak: There is a problem with the steering angle calibration file. The file might be corrupt
Effect: No driving in DBW mode (?)
Aangeraden actie: Retry steering angle calibration. If that does not work please contact the aftersales department for support via the portal.

Foutcode: Steering Angle Calib Data Open Error
Omschrijving: Steering angle calibratrion data open error
Oorzaak: There is a problem with opening the steering angle calibration file. The file might be corrupt
Effect: No driving in DBW mode (?)
Aangeraden actie: Retry steering angle calibration. If that does not work please contact the aftersales departmend for support via the portal.

Foutcode: Steering Angle Calib Data Save Error
Omschrijving: Steering angle calibration data save error
Oorzaak: An error occured during the saving of the steering angle calibration data file
Effect: No driving in DBW mode (?)
Aangeraden actie: Retry steering angle calibration. If that does not work please contact the aftersales departmend for support via the portal.

Foutcode: Service Brake Calib Data File Error
Omschrijving: Service Brake calibratrion data file error
Oorzaak: A problem has been detected with the service brake calibration file and it might corrupt
Effect: The accuracy of the service brake valves might be compromised
Aangeraden actie: Retry service brake calibration. If that does not work please contact the aftersales departmend for support via the portal.

Foutcode: Service Brake Calib Data Open Error
Omschrijving: Service Brake calibratrion data open error
Oorzaak: A problem has been detected while opening the serivce brake calibration file
Effect: The accuracy of the service brake valves might be compromised
Aangeraden actie: Retry service brake calibration. If that does not work please contact the aftersales departmend for support via the portal.

Foutcode: Service Brake Calib Data Save Error
Omschrijving: Service Brake calibration data save error
Oorzaak: An error occured during the saving of the service brake calibration data file
Effect: The accuracy of the service brake valves might be compromised
Aangeraden actie: Retry service brake calibration. If that does not work please contact the aftersales departmend for support via the portal.

Omschrijving: Voltage above normal
Oorzaak: The measured voltage on pin 61 of the A connector is above the normal value
Effect: The brake pedal pressure sensor measured an invalid value. Therefore the current brake pressure on the cylinder can no longer be determined
Aangeraden actie: Check pin 61 of the A connector, check the sensor itself, check possible wiring issues (see electronic diagram for details)

Omschrijving: Voltage below normal
Oorzaak: The measured voltage on pin 61 of the A connector is below the normal value
Effect: The brake pedal pressure sensor measured an invalid value. Therefore the current brake pressure on the cylinder can no longer be determined
Aangeraden actie: Check pin 61 of the A connector, check the sensor itself, check possible wiring issues (see electronic diagram for details)

Omschrijving: Root cause unknown
Oorzaak: The controller determines an issue on pin 61 of connector A. Specific root cause can't be determined. Potential hardware, software, firmware or configuration issue
Effect: The brake pedal pressure sensor measured an invalid value. Therefore the current brake pressure on the cylinder can no longer be determined
Aangeraden actie:
- Contact the aftersales department for support via the portal

In order to facilitate adequate support please supply the following information:
1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)
2) Log file from DIM, of the faulty scenario
3) Photo or movie of the behavior or of the DIM e.g. Dashboard view, Faultcodes view, IO Check view, CAN network check view, About menu view
4) Updated software or parameter set recently, from Terberg or 3rd party systems e.g. Engine, Transmission? If so, please supply us with details.

Omschrijving: Data Erratic, Intermittent Or Incorrect
Oorzaak: The unlock request send by the DBW User in the DBW_User_04 message is not correct. (Either out of range or mismatch in data)
Effect:
The request will not be accepted and the 5th wheel cannot be unlocked in DBW mode.

Also a protective stop will be activated
Aangeraden actie: Check the DBW 5th Wheel Unlock Request in DBW_User_04 message. Check if the value is valid (0 or 1), check if the message itself is received correctly by the ATCC2

Omschrijving: Condition Exists
Oorzaak:
An untended unlock (= trailer state from coupled to not coupled without an unlock request) has been detected.

This can be a mechanical problem with the trailer actually not being connected properly or this can be an electrical problem (kingpin present sensor or lock state sensor)
Effect: This will block the 5th wheel control
Aangeraden actie:
Please check if the king present sensor (pin 46 or /and 61 of the B connector)

Please check the locked status sensor (pin 28 or / and 41 of the A connector)

If those are ok, please check if the trailer  / the connecting system is mechanically sound

Omschrijving: Expected code checksum doesn't match the actual code checksum
Oorzaak: Something went wrong when updating the  vehicle software
Effect: The vehicle will prevent operation because the proper functioning of safety functions can now not be guaranteed
Aangeraden actie: Update software to latest version

Omschrijving: Expected code checksum doesn't match the actual code checksum
Aangeraden actie: Update software to latest version

Omschrijving: Application Data Synchronization Error
Oorzaak: There is a mismatch between the software on the standard PLC and the safety PLC. This can be caused by an error during a software update or an interrupted software update.
Effect: The controller wont start and wont get past the initialisation stage. The vehicle will not be usable
Aangeraden actie: Please try to update the software again with a thumbdrive via the DIM. Please validatie if the correct software package is loaded on the thumbdrive.

Omschrijving: The fire extinguishers power has been cut and is not powered.
Aangeraden actie: Check fuse, connector and system

Omschrijving:
The fire extinguisher has been activated and service is needed.

The vehicle speed will be limited until serviced.
Aangeraden actie: Replace system and reset system via fire extinguisher menu

Omschrijving: Abnormal Update Rate
Oorzaak: This can have various causes such as bus problems (AT1) or hardware problems
Effect:
The DBW User will not have control of the vehicle anymore.

In manual mode: It will not be possible to switch to DBW Mode

In DBW Mode: A protective stop will be activated
Aangeraden actie: Apply key cycle to restore communication and / or check AT1 CAN connection

Omschrijving: Antivalent error detected in left wheel proximity sensor
Oorzaak: Signal 1 and/or signal 2 is shorted to battery or ground.
Effect: Safe vehicle speed is invalid resulting in protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check proximity sensor and wiring

Omschrijving: CORA velocity determined with the left wheel inputs
Oorzaak: Invalid wheel speed or invalid steering angle
Effect: Safe vehicle speed is invalid resulting in protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check steering angle sensor, wiring and/or steering calibration

Omschrijving: Antivalent error detected in right wheel proximity sensor
Oorzaak: Signal 1 and/or signal 2 is shorted to battery or ground.
Effect: Safe vehicle speed is invalid resulting in protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check proximity sensor and wiring

Omschrijving: The driver has intervented the DBW operation via manual takeover button
Oorzaak: The safety driver intervened by pressing the manual take over button
Effect: A driver intervention will be triggered causing a protective stop or a switch to manual mode depending on the vehicle speed
Aangeraden actie: Please ensure that the environment is safe and clear and then continue driving

Omschrijving: CORA velocity determined with the right wheel inputs
Oorzaak: Invalid wheel speed or invalid steering angle
Effect: Safe vehicle speed is invalid resulting in protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check steering angle sensor, wiring and/or steering calibration

Omschrijving: Velocity is detected on only 1 wheel instead of both wheels
Oorzaak: CORA velocity determined based on left or right wheel is equal to 0 km/h while the other wheel unequal to 0 km/h for at least 300 ms
Effect: Safe vehicle speed is invalid resulting in protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: check everything that can influence the circumference of the front wheels e.g. tire pressure, tire wear, tire size but also the A/B pulse ring

Omschrijving: Drive direction based on individual wheels unequal
Oorzaak: Drive direction based on individual wheels are unequal for at least 5 seconds
Effect: Safe vehicle speed is invalid resulting in protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Check wheel speed A/B sensor and wiring

Omschrijving: Maximum vehicle speed of 25 km/h exceeded
Oorzaak: Vehicle speed higher than maximum vehicle speed of 25 km/h + 10%
Effect: Protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie: Please do not exceed the maximum allowed speed

Omschrijving: Cross reference failure
Oorzaak:
Left or right wheel A/B pulse sensor failure.

Left or right wheel steering angle sensor failure.
Effect: Protective stop in DBW mode
Aangeraden actie:
First check left and right wheel A/B pulse sensors.

Second check Left and right wheel steering angle sensors.

Omschrijving: An error related with safety systems was set by the device, but without a valid fault code description.
Oorzaak: Software related fault. This error is set as backup when a fault is set, but is lacking information about the cause (in the code)
Effect: Unknown, can be anything
Aangeraden actie: Always contact the software engineering department when seeing this fault

Omschrijving: Data error
Oorzaak: At least one of the signals in ATCC2 14 message is out of range
Effect: When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the ATCC2 is sending the ATCC2 14 message contents correctly.

Omschrijving: Message time-out
Oorzaak: ATCC2 14 message has not been received anymore for over 60 ms.
Effect: When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the ATCC2 is sending the ATCC2 14 message at the correct update rate of 20ms

Omschrijving: crc or message counter error
Oorzaak: The CRC check or counter value of the ATCC2 14 message is incorrect.
Effect: When in DBW mode a protective stop is triggered.
Aangeraden actie: Please check if the ATCC2 is sending the ATCC2 14 message CRC and counter correctly

Omschrijving: Data error
Oorzaak: At least one of the signals in ATCC2 15 message is out of range

Bus load warning
Oorzaak: CAN bus load exceeded 80%
Effect: Communication reliability on the CAN becomes critical. Data transmitted on the CAN bus can get lost.
Aangeraden actie:
'- Contact the aftersales department for support via the portal

In order to facilitate adequate support please supply the following information:
1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)
2) Log file from DIM, of the faulty scenario
3) Photo or movie of the behavior or of the DIM e.g. Dashboard view, Faultcodes view, IO Check view, CAN network check view, About menu view
4) Updated software or parameter set recently, from Terberg or 3rd party systems e.g. Engine, Transmission? If so, please supply us with details.

Omschrijving: Bus off
Oorzaak: Possibly a wire break, missing terminal resistor or a component added to the CAN bus which is transmitting on a different Baud rate than 250k
Effect: No communication is possible on this CAN bus. The vehicle cannot be operated properly.
Aangeraden actie: Please check the wiring of this CAN bus. of the ATCC2 Pin 48 is CAN low, and pin 49 is CAN high. You can also measure the resistance of the CAN bus when the vehicle is turned off. The resistance should be 60 Ohm. When this is 120 Ohm, a terminal resistor can be missing. If the wiring and resistance is all ok, you could disconnect components from the CAN bus one by one, and check when the error gets resolved. If it gets resolved after disconnecting a component, probably the baud rate of this component is wrong.

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 148 : Yaw rate cross check (aq-yaw)
Aangeraden actie: Check the ABS-ECU concerning correct EOL-parameter (steering ratio, wheelbase, wheel diameter, etc.) Check, whether the ESC-module is assembled in correct position Replace the ESC-module;

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 147 : Temporary esc deactivation
Aangeraden actie: Situation 1) The ESC function was temporary not available (e.g. missing external data) It is not necessary to repair the ABS/ESC-System, if no other failures are stored in the memory  Situation 2) This means, that an ESC sensorfailure was detected in the last ignition cycle Read the failure memory and repair the stored ESC-failures Remove the failurecode (by special driving procedures, by diagnostic routines, etc.);

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 145 : Esc parameterset faulty | 134 : faulty esc system configuration (detected by esc-module) | 29 : faulty esc system configuration (detected by abs ecu)
Aangeraden actie: A right combination of ABS-ECU and ESC-module must be assembled in the vehicle.;

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 154 : Reserved esc failurebit | 153 : reserved esc failurebit | 144 : reserved esc failurebit
Aangeraden actie: check/ replace the ESC-module check/ replace the ABS-ECU;

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 129 : Esc module undervoltage detection
Aangeraden actie: Check the wiring and connectors (voltage supply) of the ESC-module Check and replace the ESC-module;

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 31 : Busoff status can/ warning status can (internal esc brake system can)
Aangeraden actie: Check the CAN connection between ESC-module and ABS-ECU (short circuits);

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 152 : Yawrate sign plausibility(extended)
Aangeraden actie: Check correct mounting direction (assembly position) of ESC-module Check and replace ESC-module Check and replace steering anglesensor;

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 135 : Faulty esc module mounting
Aangeraden actie: Check the ABS-ECU concerning correct ESC specific EOL parameters (e.g. wrong sign of lateral acceleration) check the assembly position of ESC module check the assembly position of steering wheel sensor (wrong sign);

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 3 : Esc barcode failure (part 1 and 2)
Aangeraden actie: vehicle specific parameters have been changed and if this failure is displayed furthermore, then the ESC-calibration procedure must be started by diagnosis. Then the necessary adaption-values are determined again.  If the ABS-ECU or the ESC-module have been replaced, then the ESC-calibration procedure alsomust be started by diagnosis (determination of necessary adaption-values).;

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 146 : Esc parameterset/ transmission delayed | 139 : detection of intermediate axle message checksum failure (by esc-module) | 138 : detection of intermediate axle message timeout failure (by esc-module) | 137 : detection of rear axle message checksum failure (by esc-module) | 136 : detection of rear axle message timeout failure (by esc-module) | 128 : detection of abs-ecu message checksum failure (by esc-module) | 127 : detection of abs-ecu message timeout failure (by esc-module) | 25 : esc message checksum detection | 16 : esc message timeout detection
Aangeraden actie: Check ABS-ECU for correct EOL-configuration (ESC yes/no)  Check the wiring between ABS-ECU and ESC-module  Check and replace the ESC-module Check and replace the ABS-ECU;

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 151 : Yawrate plausibility (straight on)
Aangeraden actie: Check/ replace ESC-module Check/ replace steering angle sensor;

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 433 : Esc can message blockdata check | 132 : check of internal devices in esc-module | 131 : check of eeprom in esc-module | 125 : check of yaw rate sensor in esc-module | 124 : check of lateral acceleration sensor in esc-module
Aangeraden actie: RCheck the assembly position, the lateral inclination and correct fixing of the ESC-module Check and replace the ESC module (correct assembly position is important) emark: Was the vehicle standing on a moving surface (ferry, train-transport, etc.) with activated ignition ? This might probably cause such a failurecode. The ignition should be switched off in such a situation.;

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 432 : Check of correct esc parameters (esc module yes/no) | 133 : esc parameter failure (detected by esc-module) | 105 : check of correct esc parameters (invalid wheelbase/ invalid vehicle type/ invalid steering type of 3rd axle/ invalid characteristic of steering ratio)
Aangeraden actie: Check the ABS-ECU concerning correct EOL parameters (related toESC function);

Foutcode: Electronic Stability Control System (CAN Data Link/ ESC Module)
Omschrijving: 130 : Esc initialisation not completed
Aangeraden actie: The ESC calibration-procedure must be executed by use of the diagnostic documentation.;

In manual mode: You are probably unable to go to DBW mode since the PVED has an error and will probably not finish the preparation phase.

In DBW mode: Probably the automatic steering will fail, causing a protective stop
Aangeraden actie: Check if the sasa sensor is still operational. Check if the data send by the sensor is valid. Check if the crosscheck result is valid

Foutcode: Auxiliary steering device Steering angle crosscheck
Omschrijving: Error in cross check of Auxilary steering device
Oorzaak:
1. AUX mini wheel steering angle deviation too high between primary and 
redundant signal 
2. Transmit rate of primary and redundant signal deviate too much from each 
other 
3. P3371 & P3372 settings does not fit to the AUX mini wheel device
Effect:
In manual mode: You are probably unable to go to DBW mode since the PVED has an error and will probably not finish the preparation phase.

In DBW mode: Probably the automatic steering will fail, causing a protective stop
Aangeraden actie:
Please check if the main and redundant signal crosscheck is within the accepted boundaries.

By using the Plus1 tool, check if parameter P3371 and P3372 are ok for the used AUX device

In manual mode: You are probably unable to go to DBW mode since the PVED has an error and will probably not finish the preparation phase.

Aangeraden actie: Please check, by using the Plus1 tool, on which value the parameters mentioned in the Cause column are set and if there is a mismatch between them

Omschrijving: WAS CAN Sensor exceeded calibration limit
Oorzaak:
1. Wheel angle sensors are not calibrated properly.
2. Vehicle geometry has changed and it is now possible to steer the wheels 
further than the calibrated max points.
3. Mechanical link integrity lost
Effect:
In manual mode: You are probably unable to go to DBW mode since the PVED has an error and will probably not finish the preparation phase.

In DBW mode: Probably the automatic steering will fail, causing a protective stop
Aangeraden actie: Please try to recalibrate the steering system by using the DIM. If the problem still persists afterwards, please verifry the mechanical integrity of the steering system

Foutcode: Auxiliary steering device Joystick position crosscheck
Omschrijving: Auxilary Joystick Position cross check fail
Oorzaak:

redundant signal

Effect:

Foutcode: Auxiliary steering device Joystick trim value crosscheck
Omschrijving: Auxiliary steering device Joystick trim value crosscheck
Oorzaak:
1. AUX Joystick trim signal deviation too high between primary and 
redundant signal 
2. Transmit rate of primary and redundant signal deviate too much from each 
other 
3. P3388 & P3389 settings does not fit to the AUX joystick
Effect:
In manual mode: You are probably unable to go to DBW mode since the PVED has an error and will probably not finish the preparation phase.

In DBW mode: Probably the automatic steering will fail, causing a protective stop
Aangeraden actie:
Check if there is deviation between the primary and the redundant signal of the joystick and check if this deviation exceeds the limit.

Please check if parameter P3387 is configured correctly (to use joystick) via the Plus1 tool
